<meta name="Title" content="Seattle Department of Transportation: Seattle Bicycle Master Plan">
<meta name="Description" content="Seattle Department of Transportation: SDOT's Bicycle Program has been working steadily toward developing an urban trail system to accommodate bicyclists. Urban trails include shared use paths, bike lanes, signed bike routes, arterials with wide shoulders, and pedestrian pathways. Seattle has about 28 miles of shared use paths, 22 miles of on-street, striped bike lanes, and about 90 miles of signed bike routes.">
